        "content": "<p>SebTardif opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13943\">PR #13943</a> from <code>SebTardif:fix/riscv64-stack-switch-sp</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h2>Summary</h2>\n<p>Applies the same stack-switch fix as #13883 to riscv64: decrement <code>sp</code> before storing callee-saved registers so writes land in reserved stack space.</p>\n<p>Closes #13884</p>\n<h2>Why</h2>\n<p>Issue #13884 notes riscv64 still stores below SP before the <code>addi</code>, which can race with signal handlers (same root cause as the riscv32imac fix).</p>\n<h2>Test plan</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>[x] Diff matches the #13883 offset pattern (reserve <code>0xd0</code>, then positive offsets for <code>sd</code>/<code>fsd</code>)</li>\n<li>[ ] CI fiber/stackswitch jobs for riscv64</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>",
